result.execSummary:
The defendant Vincent J Hartel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs of the action have been paid in full.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Vincent J Hartel in court. Nicholas Grode appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State advises of Defendant's progress completing the agreement, moves to amend the charge to forfeiture disorderly conduct. Court amends charge, imposes costs of the action.

Defendant Vincent J Hartel in court, in custody. Nicholas Grode appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court clarifies that Defendant turned himself in based as a result of warrant entered 9/11, reviews previous activity. State advises of discussions with Defendant regarding proof of completion of conditions, believes those things have been completed but Defendant did not have proof. After receiving proof of compliance, State believes agreement will be completed.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for September 25, 2017 at 11:30 am.
Bench warrant was issued by Judge Weber not Judge Ehlers. Clerk not able to change court record.

Defendant Vincent J Hartel not in court.  Nicholas Grode appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case called at 11:07 am. Non appearance by defendant.  Court reviews events in file. State indicates defendant hasn't complied with terms of DAGPA, request warrant be issued. Court orders bench warrant to ECAR region.
$500 cash bond posted covers costs ($181.50). $318.50 will be refunded at conclusion of case.

Defendant Vincent J Hartel in court. Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court questions Defendant on continued waiver of right to Counsel, finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver. State advises of plea agreement. Court reviews charges, max. penalties, elements. Defendant enters guilty plea to Count 2. Court questions Defendant on rights, finds plea made freely and voluntarily, finds basis to accepts pleas, withholds acceptance of plea, reviews conditions contained within DAGPA, approves DAGPA. Count 1 is dismissed but read in for sentencing. State advises of reasoning for agreement. Court questions victim. State advises that case can be resolved via written stipulation if all conditions are successfully completed. Bond continues as is.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for September 11, 2017 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Vincent J Hartel in court. Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Copy of Complaint given to Defendant in Court. Court reviews charges, max. penalties, right to counsel.   Defendant wants to try to resolve matter with DA, waives right to Counsel. Court questions Defendant, finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver. Defendant to make appointment with DA. Bond set.  Status conference scheduled for August 23, 2016 at 10:00 am.
